1. Authentication backend issue (most likely if SSH accepted connections)

If SSH port was reachable but login never completed:

LDAP/AD server unreachable

DNS resolution issue

SSSD hung

PAM authentication timeout


Check whether SSSD is being used:

grep passwd /etc/nsswitch.conf
grep group /etc/nsswitch.conf

systemctl status sssd

Look for June 12 logs:

zgrep "2026-06-12" /var/log/auth.log*
zgrep "2026-06-12" /var/log/secure*

Depending on distro one of these files exists.


---

2. Disk space exhaustion

When /, /var, or /run become full:

Existing sessions keep working.

New logins fail or hang.

Services become unresponsive.


Check current state:

df -h
df -i

And search for June 12 filesystem errors:

grep "2026-06-12" /var/log/syslog | grep -i "no space"
grep "2026-06-12" /var/log/syslog | grep -i "read-only"


---

3. Process exhaustion

If the host hit PID limits:

fork: retry: Resource temporarily unavailable

new SSH logins fail while the machine still pings and accepts TCP connections.

Search:

grep -i "Resource temporarily unavailable" /var/log/syslog
grep -i "fork" /var/log/syslog


